author: cbs8
title: Harbor filled with Katrina debris cleaned
text:
BAY ST. LOUIS, Miss. (AP) - More than 10 years after Hurricane Katrina, storm debris still litters the marshlands of Hancock County.
A joint cleanup effort this week in Clermont Harbor targeted the mess Katrina left behind. Mississippi Power, Coast Electric, the city of Waveland and Hancock County's beautification committee are among the partners handling the cleanup.
WLOX-TV reports ( http://bit.ly/1LmN5NG ) an old washing machine, several boats and a couple of bath tubs were among the debris removed from the harbor's marshes.
Craig Clement, of the Clermont Harbor Civic Association, says anything that came out of people's homes, ended up in the harbor.
Waveland officials hope to follow up the effort with similar cleanup projects. Waveland's beautification director, Don Siebenkittel, says the city still has a lot of boats and debris in wooded areas.
Information from: WLOX-TV, http://www.wlox.com
